==Old English==
===Etymology===
From West Germanic ''*manōn-'', from Indo-European ''*men-'' ‘think’.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[monia]], Old Saxon [[manon|manōn]] (Dutch [[manen]]), Old High German [[manon|manōn]].  The IE root is also the source of Greek [[μενος]], Latin [[mens]], Welsh [[mynnu]], Russian [[мнить]], Lithuanian [[minti]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'manian/

===Verb===
'''manian''' (class 2 weak)
# to bring to mind what should be done or what should not be forgotten; to [[urge]], to [[admonish]]

